node.text: Some Friday thoughts....✨The greatest thing that comes along with age is feeling truly comfortable in your skin. 💫 Getting to know who you really are takes time! I would have never guessed it could take 3 decades but I’m grateful for every part of that evolution. ✨ And through every stage, the ice and skating has been there for me. During good or bad times, it was always “home” and always will be. It’s also where I’ve never felt out of place. Life throws a lot at you and to find a space where you feel whole and free is something I will never take for granted. 💫 I still look forward to many more years of learning and growing....all while having my “home” to escape to. 📽 @carlottaedwards #lakeskating #alberta #lakelouise #figureskating #banff #outdoorskating

node.text:
I have ALWAYS wanted to skate on an outdoor lake. Especially Lake Louise. 🧊✔️ So lucky for these few minutes of improv surrounded by this crazy beautiful scenery. After a long day of shooting and shivering from the cold, I got lost in my favorite little world and got to do what I love most. 🙌🏻 The ice started melting the day before we arrived but slushy, rutted and bumpy ice didn’t scare me. ⚔️ (Maybe it did a little, definitely not use to that but walked away in one piece. So it was more than worth it!) I’m thankful @carlottaedwards said “Quick, before we run to our next location - Skate for a minute! You will want to remember this”  She was so right! She is also so good behind a 🎥 @arianagrande 

#outdoorskating #lakelouise #lakelouisecanada #banff #alberta #iceskating #lakeskating #canada #figureskating #arianagrande #frozenlake #lakeskating

node.text: On this day my dream came true💫 4 minutes changed my life forever and in those 4 minutes I felt so many emotions. I felt immense nerves and pressure but the only emotion I really remember is pure joy. I loved every single second of being out there. Every skater knows the magic of a performance where everything falls into place and you feel like you’re flying. Goodness I love this sport so much. #olympics #figureskating

node.title: February 20th will always hold magic for me.

node.text: Every Olympics we do a room tour! Showing you where we will be for the next month and some of our favorite things! 💗💗💗 @loveshackfancy @misa_losangeles @aliceandolivia @farmrio @dressthepopulation @goldengoose @slipsilkpillowcase @quinnsnacks @mmschocolate @hukitchen @slipsilkpillowcase @laneige_us @biossance @youthtothepeople @summerfridays @philipssonicare

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tara Lipinski in Tokyo Japan.

node.text: When I walked out on my balcony and saw these rings, I felt a rush of adrenaline and a flood of giddiness. The only thing I can liken it to is the feeling I got as a kid when I opened my hotel window and saw Disney World off in the distance. 6 Olympics, 4 with NBC. I’m so privileged and honored to be a part of this event. ✨ I can’t wait to bust through my adjoining room door and wake up @johnnygweir first thing in the morning! ✨
A summer night in France. 🇫🇷❤️ Always at my happiest in Europe.

node.text: Finally got to return the favor to Todd after so many incredible surprise birthdays he’s thrown for me. His friend Chad showed up on his doorstep and I got us a party bus (Triggering subject for Todd. He planned one for my bday but long story short, it didn’t show. So just had to get one for his) for a day of brewery hopping in Torrance.🍺Shout out to @commonspacela (my favorite stop of the day!) 🍻

node.text: It’s my TK’s birthday! Goodness, I love him. I love so many things about this man. His laugh, his creativity, his thoughtfulness, his brains, his jump shot, the beats he creates, the way he calls out “where’s my birdy”, the way he loves our Sully, the way he loved our Dublin, the way he pats the top of my head, the way I have to get on my tip toes to kiss him….the list could go on and on. You get the point, I love my Tk. I hope this birthday brings him everything he wishes for! @toddkap

node.text: 4 years.✨That day I never felt happier. I was so ready to marry my @toddkap ✨These pictures capture exactly how I felt. It really was just the most awesome feeling of pure joy and happiness. I can’t imagine my life without him. Every milestone, each up and down that life throws at us, we get through it together and I can’t imagine it any other way. It has been terrible to lose Dublin but Todd’s sweetness and support has made me love him even more. ✨ Also had to add Dubby to this. (His little blue bow tie 🥰)

node.text: Happy Fathers to this guy! I’m not sure how I got so lucky. To the best dad out there, thank you for ALWAYS being there for me, whatever the issue (big or small.) You not only generously offer all the advice and solutions but you hear my every worry out without ever making me feel crazy. 😂
